Article 1. Definitions

1.1 "Software" means all components of the ProtoCloak software, including
    but not limited to binary executables, configuration files,
    documentation, and related materials.
1.2 "User" means any natural person or legal entity that obtains,
    installs, or uses the Software.
1.3 "Applicable Law" means the laws and regulations in force in the
    country or jurisdiction in which the User uses the Software.
1.4 "Software Fee" means any fee charged to any third party for the
    Software itself, including but not limited to license fees, usage
    fees, access fees, download fees, delivery fees, resale fees, or any
    arrangement that requires a third party to pay in order to obtain,
    receive, or use the Software.
1.5 "Services" means value-added services provided by the User in relation
    to the Software, including installation, deployment, configuration,
    integration, operation, hosting, monitoring, training, and technical
    support.
1.6 "Service Fees" means fees charged for Services, and not Software Fees
    charged for the Software itself.
1.7 "Based on the Software" means directly or indirectly using the
    Software or any portion of it (including its binaries, configuration,
    documentation, or other materials) to copy, modify, adapt, translate,
    create derivative works, combine, or to implement substantially
    similar functionality using information obtained through
    reverse-engineering of the Software. For the avoidance of doubt,
    independent development (developed from scratch without copying the
    Software, without using any non-public materials of the Software, and
    without using information obtained through reverse-engineering of the
    Software) is not "Based on the Software".
1.8 "Official Repository" means the code hosting repository designated by
    the copyright holder for publishing official information and official
    releases of the Software. The Official Repository at the time of
    publication of this Agreement is: `https://github.com/qianfan75/ProtoCloak`.
    The copyright holder may change the Official Repository by publishing
    a notice in the Official Repository or by releasing a new version of
    the Software.
1.9 "Unmodified Binary Files" means binary executable files whose
    executable contents are byte-for-byte identical to the corresponding
    version released via the Official Repository. For the avoidance of
    doubt, packaging, compressing, archiving, renaming, providing checksum
    files (e.g., SHA256), or providing digital signatures, without
    altering the executable contents, does not constitute a "modification";
    however, any act that alters the executable contents (including but
    not limited to patching, rewriting, instrumenting, re-linking,
    stripping symbols, obfuscating, or replacing the executable via an
    installer or script) constitutes a "modification".
1.10 "Compute Time" means the duration during which a device is actively
     processing computational tasks while communicating through the Software,
     measured from the establishment to the termination of the connection
     between the device and the Software.

Article 2. Free Distribution

2.1 The Software is provided to Users free of charge. Any party charging
    any Software Fee to any third party is in violation of this
    Agreement.
2.2 The Software is distributed solely in binary executable form.
2.3 For the avoidance of doubt, this Agreement does not prohibit the User
    from providing Services to third parties and charging Service Fees,
    and does not prohibit the User from operating or hosting the Software
    to provide services to third parties; however, the User shall not
    market, bundle, or otherwise charge any Service Fees as a Software
    Fee in disguise.

Article 3. Grant of Rights

Subject to compliance with all terms of this Agreement, the copyright
holder grants the User a non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable
right to:

3.0 By downloading, installing, running, or otherwise using the Software,
    the User is deemed to have read, understood, and agreed to be bound
    by all terms of this Agreement, and agrees to assume all risks and
    responsibilities arising from the use of the Software.

3.1 Use the Software for the protection and proxying of Stratum protocol
    communications;
3.2 Deploy and configure the Software within infrastructure owned or
    lawfully managed by the User;
3.3 Distribute unmodified binary files to third parties. The distributor
    shall make this Agreement available to third parties (or provide an
    accessible copy) before download, installation, or use, and shall
    clearly state that "use constitutes acceptance" of this Agreement.
3.4 For the avoidance of doubt, the User may re-distribute, mirror, or
    re-host unmodified binary files (for example, by providing downloads
    via other websites or storage services) provided that all of the
    following conditions are met:
    (a) clearly and prominently state that such distribution is not from
        the Official Repository and does not represent an official release;
    (b) clearly and prominently provide a reference to the Official
        Repository so third parties can obtain official releases and
        verification information;
    (c) include this Agreement in full and preserve all copyright notices,
        trademarks, and other proprietary markings contained in the Software;
    (d) no Software Fees are charged.

Article 4. Restrictions

The User shall not:

4.1 Except to the extent expressly permitted by Applicable Law, modify,
    decompile, disassemble, or otherwise reverse-engineer the Software;
4.2 Create, develop, or distribute competing Stratum protocol proxy
    software products that are Based on the Software;
4.3 Operate or host the Software for third parties on the condition that
    any Software Fee is charged to such third parties;
4.4 Remove or alter any copyright notices, trademarks, or other
    proprietary markings contained in the Software;
4.5 Charge any Software Fee, or distribute, deliver, resell, rent, or
    license the Software in any paid form.

Article 5. Lawful Use

5.1 The User shall ensure that all use of the Software fully complies
    with Applicable Law.
5.2 The Software shall not be used for any purpose that violates
    Applicable Law, including but not limited to money laundering,
    fraud, unauthorized access to computer systems, or any other
    unlawful activity.
5.3 The User bears sole responsibility for determining whether their use
    of the Software is lawful. The copyright holder assumes no liability
    for any consequences arising from the User's unlawful use of the
    Software.
    For the avoidance of doubt, if the User uses the Software for any
    unlawful purpose or in the course of any unlawful activity, the User
    shall bear all legal responsibility and consequences under the laws
    and jurisdiction of the country or region in which the Software is
    used.
5.4 The Software does not collect, log, store, or transmit to the
    copyright holder or any third party any personally identifying
    information or financial information of the User.
5.5 Any processing and forwarding of network data performed by the
    Software is limited to what is necessary for its intended purpose,
    including proxying and protecting Stratum protocol communications and
    the donation mechanism described in Article 6, and is determined by
    the User's configuration and runtime environment.
5.6 Configuration and operational data required for the Software to
    function is stored under the User's control on the User's systems.
    Except as expressly required by Applicable Law or expressly stated
    otherwise in this Agreement, the Software does not include telemetry,
    statistics, or analytics uploading to the copyright holder.

Article 6. Donation Mechanism

6.1 The Software contains a built-in automatic mechanism that makes a
    gratuitous donation to the copyright holder based on 0.5% of the
    total Compute Time of devices operating through the Software, to
    support the ongoing development and maintenance of the Software. For
    the avoidance of doubt, "Compute Time" is defined in Article 1.10,
    and "total Compute Time" means the aggregate Compute Time of all
    devices operating through the Software, as internally measured and
    accounted for by the Software. For reference only, 0.5%
    is approximately 432 seconds per 24 hours; this figure is an
    approximation and is not a guarantee.
6.2 The donation under this Article is not a Software Fee and is not a
    condition for the grant of rights to use the Software under this
    Agreement.
6.3 By using the Software, the User acknowledges and agrees to the
    existence of this donation mechanism and agrees to make the
    gratuitous donation specified in this Article, and undertakes not to
    bypass, disable, modify, or remove it in any way.
6.4 Any attempt to circumvent the provisions of this Article constitutes
    a material breach of this Agreement.

Article 7. Disclaimer of Warranty

THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS
OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY,
FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT. THE USER ASSUMES
ALL RISK ASSOCIATED WITH THE USE OF THE SOFTWARE.

Article 8. Limitation of Liability

8.1 IN NO EVENT SHALL THE COPYRIGHT HOLDER BE LIABLE FOR ANY DIRECT,
    INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, PUNITIVE, OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES,
    LOSSES, OR LIABILITIES ARISING OUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE USE OF
    OR INABILITY TO USE THE SOFTWARE, WHETHER BASED ON CONTRACT, TORT,
    STRICT LIABILITY, OR ANY OTHER LEGAL THEORY, EVEN IF THE COPYRIGHT
    HOLDER HAS BEEN ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH DAMAGES.
8.2 WITHOUT LIMITING THE GENERALITY OF SECTION 8.1, THE COPYRIGHT HOLDER
    SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY LOST PROFITS, LOSS OF REVENUE, LOSS OF
    DATA, BUSINESS INTERRUPTION, OR ANY OTHER ECONOMIC LOSS ARISING FROM
    THE USE OF THE SOFTWARE.
8.3 The copyright holder shall not be liable for any legal consequences
    arising from the User's use of the Software in violation of
    Applicable Law.

Article 9. Termination

9.1 If the User breaches any term of this Agreement, this Agreement shall
    not terminate immediately. The User is granted a 30-day grace period
    to cure such breach. The grace period shall be calculated from the
    date the User becomes aware (or reasonably should have become aware)
    of the breach. If the User cures the breach within the grace period
    and remains in compliance, this Agreement shall continue in effect.
9.2 If, after the grace period expires, the User fails to cure the
    breach, is unable to cure it, or refuses to cure it, the copyright
    holder may revoke the license granted under this Agreement, and this
    Agreement shall terminate upon expiry of the grace period.
9.3 Upon termination, the User must immediately cease using the Software
    and, within a reasonable time and using reasonable efforts, delete,
    destroy, or render unusable all copies of the Software under the
    User's control (including copies made for distribution). For backup
    copies created automatically as part of the User's normal backup
    processes that cannot reasonably be individually identified or
    immediately deleted, the User may retain such backup copies for the
    ordinary backup retention period, provided that the User does not
    restore, use, or re-distribute them, and deletes or overwrites them
    upon expiry of the retention period or when feasible.
9.4 Articles 5, 7, 8, and 9 shall survive termination of this Agreement.

Article 10. General Provisions

10.1 This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the parties
     regarding the Software and supersedes all prior oral or written
     understandings.
10.2 If any provision of this Agreement is found to be invalid or
     unenforceable, the remaining provisions shall remain in full force
     and effect.
10.3 This Agreement shall remain in effect from the date of its initial
     publication and shall apply to all subsequent versions of the
     Software, unless expressly superseded by a new version of this
     Agreement published by the copyright holder.
10.4 This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with
     the laws of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region. Any dispute
     arising out of or in connection with this Agreement shall be
     submitted to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of the Hong
     Kong Special Administrative Region.
10.5 For Users who are consumers under the law of the European Union,
     nothing in this Agreement shall exclude or limit the application of
     mandatory provisions of the law of the Member State of their habitual
     residence, particularly regarding consumer protection and liability
     for gross negligence or willful misconduct.
